      <item>
        <title>Error deploying to Heroku</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[juanma]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>HI <a class="mention" href="https://community.frontity.org/u/nicolasboada">@nicolasboada</a> ,</p>
<p>Heroku works within a git repository. It seems you are not working inside one</p>
<p>As indicated in the <a href="https://docs.frontity.org/deployment/deploy-on-heroku">Heroku guide</a></p>
<blockquote>
<p>The Heroku CLI requires Git, the popular version control system. If you don’t already have Git installed, complete the following before proceeding: <a href="https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2/Getting-Started-Installing-Git">Git installation</a> &amp; <a href="https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2/Getting-Started-First-Time-Git-Setup">First-time Git setup</a></p>
</blockquote>
<p>Once you have <code>git</code> properly installed and configured you can initialize any Git repository on any folder by doing <a href="https://www.atlassian.com/git/tutorials/setting-up-a-repository/git-init"><code>git init</code></a></p>
<p>Hope this helps</p>
          <p><a href="https://community.frontity.org/t/error-deploying-to-heroku/4083/3">Read full topic</a></p>
        ]]></description>
